6:
That is a lot of ground meat. I
imagine we'll be having hamburgers
for dinner.
10:
Ooh, so close! I was actually thinking
of making cabbage rolls today.
31:
Don't go surprising me like that, all
right?!
35:
Were you also shopping for dinner,
Karyl?
38: I guess you could say that, yeah.
44:
But aren't you going in the wrong
direction? That leads out of
Palpebra.
48:
Sh-shut up! I know! Just leave me
alone.
53:
And don't tell anybody about this,
you hear?!
69: Huh. Well, this should be fun.
75: Is she practicing her magic again?
79:
Okay, guys, have you been
behaving? Who's hungry?
83:
Come on, come on, don't be
greedy—there's enough for
everyone!
92:
I don't think I've ever seen her with
such a big grin on her face!
103: I also wish to play with the kittens.
107:
Not sure that's a good idea—if Karyl
finds us here we're basically as
good as dead.
111:
Plus, we don't want to interrupt her
while she's having such a good time.
Let's head home. You can play with
the kittens later!
124:
Gya! You two?! Why are you here?
How long have you been watching
me?!
129:
Never mind that! I'll take care of
these monsters. Karyl, you protect
the kittens!
144: I will! Take care of the rest for me.
154:
How DARE you lay a hand on my
precious kitties?! DIE!
160:
Thankfully, you seem to be mostly
uninjured. The kittens are all safe as
well.
165: Are these... all your kittens, Karyl?
170:
No, they're not mine! I just... found
them here a few days ago, while I
was practicing.
172:
They were separated from their
mom and were all frail and... I had to
do SOMETHING!
177:
But there was no reason to hide
them like this! Didn't you tell anyone
from the Gourmet Guild?
181:
No way, they're all working so hard
to find a way back to Landosol—they
don't have time to look after kittens!
186: Would they be opposed to it?
189:
Probably not... Which is why I can't
ask them to do that!
193:
A-anyway! I'll take care of these
kittens by myself, so don't go telling
anyone else, okay?!
197:
All right. We won't.
We promise.
204:
Oh. You finally came to get them,
huh.
207:
Don't look at me like that! Follow
your mom closely, or you'll get lost
just like last time!
211:
What? No need to worry about me,
I'm all grown-up, I can take care of
myself! Get going!
222:
Oh. You're... in a surprisingly good
mood.
225:
Well, duh! What do you mean
"surprisingly"?
227:
I mean, the kittens you were looking
after just left... I figured you might be
sad about it!
229: No way. If anything, I'm overjoyed.
232:
They looked really happy to be
reunited with their mom. I'm sure
she was worried sick about them
too.
235:
Children love their parents, after all...
And parents—no matter what they
may say—love their children too.
242:
I'm in a great mood! You two, come
with me!
245:
I'll buy your silence about today's
events by treating you to a delicious
meal! Consider yourselves lucky.
250:
Cabbage rolls will have to be
tomorrow, I suppose.
260:
Enough chitchat, let's get going!
Hehe.
